.TH ACE.CONF 5 "2026-07-19" "Ace 0.1.0" "Arcturus Linux"
.SH NAME
ace.conf \- Ace package manager configuration
.SH DESCRIPTION
Ace reads
.B /etc/ace.conf
by default. Use
.B \-\-pacman
to read
.B /etc/pacman.conf
and use pacman-compatible paths instead. The format is identical to
.BR pacman.conf (5).

.SH FILE FORMAT
The configuration file is an INI-style file with sections denoted by
[brackets]. Lines beginning with # are comments. Keys and values are
separated by =.

.PP
Two section types exist:
.B [options]
for global settings and
.B [repo-name]
for repository definitions.

.SH OPTIONS SECTION
.TP
\fBRootDir\fR = \fI/path\fR
Installation root directory. All operations are relative to this path.
Default: /
.TP
\fBDBPath\fR = \fI/path\fR
Path to the package database. In native mode this is /var/lib/ace/.
In \-\-pacman mode this is /var/lib/pacman/. Default: /var/lib/ace/
.TP
\fBCacheDir\fR = \fI/path\fR
Directory for cached package files. Default: /var/cache/ace/pkg/
.TP
\fBLogFile\fR = \fI/path\fR
Transaction log file path. Default: /var/log/ace.log
.TP
\fBGPGDir\fR = \fI/path\fR
GPG home directory for signature verification and keyring storage.
Default: /etc/ace/gnupg/
.TP
\fBHookDir\fR = \fI/path\fR
Directory containing ALPM .hook files. May be specified multiple
times to include hooks from multiple directories (e.g. system hooks
and user hooks). Default: /etc/ace/hooks/
.TP
\fBHoldPkg\fR = \fIpkg1 pkg2 ...\fR
Space-separated list of packages that will never be removed. These
packages are skipped during -R unless explicitly forced.
.TP
\fBArchitecture\fR = \fIauto\fR|\fIarch\fR
Target architecture for package selection. Use \fIauto\fR to detect.
Default: auto
.TP
\fBSigLevel\fR = \fIlevel\fR ...
Signature verification level. See \fBSIGNATURE LEVELS\fR below.
.TP
\fBParallelDownloads\fR = \fIN\fR
Number of concurrent download streams. Default: 3
.TP
\fBDownloadUser\fR = \fIusername\fR
Drop privileges to this user for network downloads. Requires root.
.TP
\fBCheckSpace\fR
Enable disk space checking before transactions. Disabled by default.
.TP
\fBVerbosePkgLists\fR
Show package sizes and descriptions in package lists.
.TP
\fBColor\fR
Enable coloured output (always enabled in ace).
.TP
\fBIgnorePkg\fR = \fIpkg1 pkg2 ...\fR
Packages to ignore during upgrades.
.TP
\fBIgnoreGroup\fR = \fIgroup1 group2 ...\fR
Groups to ignore during upgrades.
.TP
\fBNoExtract\fR = \fIglob1 glob2 ...\fR
File globs that will never be extracted from packages.
.TP
\fBNoUpgrade\fR = \fIglob1 glob2 ...\fR
File globs that will be saved as .pacnew instead of overwritten.
.TP
\fBCleanMethod\fR = \fIKeepInstalled\fR|\fIKeepCurrent\fR
Determines which packages are kept during -Sc. \fIKeepInstalled\fR retains
only installed versions. \fIKeepCurrent\fR retains the current version from
the sync database. Default: KeepInstalled
.TP
\fBDisableSandbox\fR
Disable all sandboxing for downloads.
.TP
\fBI LoveCandy\fR
Accepted for compatibility; enables the candy-style progress bar.

.SH REPOSITORY SECTIONS
Each repository section may contain:
.TP
\fBServer\fR = \fIurl\fR
A full URL to the repository. Variables \fB$repo\fR and \fB$arch\fR
are substituted. May be specified multiple times for mirror failover.
.TP
\fBInclude\fR = \fI/path\fR
Include another file (typically a mirrorlist). The file is parsed
recursively; Server lines found within populate the repository.
.TP
\fBSigLevel\fR = \fIlevel\fR ...
Per-repository signature verification level override.
.TP
\fBUsage\fR = \fISync\fR|\fIAll\fR
Repository usage scope. \fISync\fR for sync operations only.
\fIAll\fR for both sync and file search.

.SH SIGNATURE LEVELS
The SigLevel directive accepts one or more of:
.TP
\fBNever\fR
No signature checking.
.TP
\fBOptional\fR
Signatures are checked if present; missing signatures are not an error.
.TP
\fBRequired\fR
Signatures are mandatory; missing or invalid signatures cause failure.
.TP
\fBTrustedOnly\fR
Only keys in the keyring are trusted.
.TP
\fBTrustAll\fR
All keys are trusted (not recommended).
.TP
\fBDatabaseOptional\fR, \fBDatabaseRequired\fR
Modifiers that apply the specified level to repository databases.
.TP
\fBPackageOptional\fR, \fBPackageRequired\fR
Modifiers that apply the specified level to individual packages.
.TP
\fBLocalFileSigLevel\fR
Signature level for local package files (-U operations).

.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
[options]
DBPath      = /var/lib/ace/
CacheDir    = /var/cache/ace/pkg/
LogFile     = /var/log/ace.log
GPGDir      = /etc/ace/gnupg/
Architecture = auto
SigLevel    = Required DatabaseOptional
ParallelDownloads = 5

[core]
Include = /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist

[extra]
Include = /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist

[multilib]
Include = /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist
.fi

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/ace.conf
Default ace configuration file (native mode).
.TP
.I /etc/pacman.conf
Pacman configuration (used when --pacman is active).
.TP
.I /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist
Repository mirror list, included by configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/ace/hooks/
Default hook directory.
.TP
.I /etc/ace/gnupg/
Default GPG keyring directory.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ace (1),
.BR pacman.conf (5),
.BR pacman (8)
